public schools and develop some joint research 
projects and some collaborative, cooperative

23:27.254 --> 23:40.610
type activities to encourage research. And so we 
had this conference and we selected eight school

23:40.630 --> 23:43.734
districts. And then we got them, asked them to make 
a commitment for the next year to kind of on a

23:45.496 --> 23:55.067
cooperative way, experimental way, to see if we 
can develop this organization. And they've

23:55.739 --> 23:58.764
developed a research project now that they're 
working on. They're collecting data on dropouts

23:58.824 --> 24:03.232
in all eight districts. And they're trying to 
analyze or collect data on the characteristics of

24:03.252 --> 24:07.559
dropouts. The next step then is that that would 
lead to intervention strategies and so on. And

24:12.848 --> 24:17.376
